The paper deals with quantum computation and its connection to lattice problems, which are central to the field of computational complexity. Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves algorithms and data structures, which are covered in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Information Theory (cs.IT) is also relevant as the paper discusses the hidden subgroup problem. Cryptography (cs.CR) is another possible sub-category as lattice problems are used in cryptography. Finally, Machine Learning (cs.LG) is a less likely sub-category as the paper does not explicitly discuss machine learning, but it does involve optimization problems which are relevant to machine learning.
